# [Dotfiles as a bare repository](https://www.atlassian.com/git/tutorials/dotfiles)

## Installation

```bash
git clone --bare git@github.com:rafamoreira/dotfiles.git $HOME/.cfg
alias config='/usr/bin/git --git-dir=$HOME/.cfg/ --work-tree=$HOME'
config checkout
```

It's a PITA to have to manage the .gitignore files if you want to show the untracked files. So you can hide them with:
```bash
config config --local status.showUntrackedFiles no
```


